A new heart will I give you and a new spirit will I put within you, and I will take away the stony heart out of your flesh and give you a heart of flesh. And I will put my Spirit within you and cause you to walk in My statutes, and you shall heed My ordinances and do them. Ezekiel 36:26,27

texts.html: Joy is defined as a feeling of great pleasure, happiness, or is “rejoice” in the sense of a verb. Like many people in the world I have struggled with depression and anxiety for numerous years and have always found explanations for the way I was feeling – whether it be my living circumstances, a boy who broke my heart, an argument I had with someone, or because of _________ I have always had a reason for my sadness. Always asking God why I got the short end of the stick in this and that situation. And because of it, or sometimes because of no reason at all, I resort to laying in bed for hours wondering “why me”. Sitting and loathing in self pity as I let Satan whisper lies into my ear or replaying hurtful words that have been said by others.

texts.html: The picture above was taking by a good friend of mine while we were at camp. That weekend was really rough for me. Insecurities I have that I didn’t even know existed came to the surface in the short 48 hours I was at camp. I cried, and I cried a lot. I cried harder than I have in awhile – but not because I felt bad for myself necessarily, but because I have let the circumstance of my life effect me so much that I allowed them to shape me into who I am and it is where I’ve let my identity lie for so many years.

texts.html: Reflect on your own life and choices before the Lord in prayer. Seek Him. Ask him for strength, and for happiness. Heck I pray multiple times a day “God, help me to be happy. Don’t let me cry or be sad over this.” His strength is shown through our weakness.

texts.html: Today everything in me wants so shut down and just lie in my bed, much like many of you reading this. Today I hope that God nudges you to get out of bed and go outside. To take a walk, to pray, to be thankful for things that you normally don’t realize. Shoot I have a nice bike with a basket. I have the cutest dog in the whole wide world. I was blessed with that weekend at camp and got to spend time with wonderful women and ride in a canoe. We can’t go back in time but my prayer for myself and for you today is that we think happy thoughts. You may have had a rough past, you may have had a bad day yesterday, but that is no excuse to stay in bondage. Get up and get out. You can do this. He can give you a new heart today.
